  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (226affb 2022-09-27T00:12:59.945754Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge fmt\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nRunning `forge fmt` from the project root respects the contents of `ignore`, running it from a subdirectory does not. For instance\r\n\r\n1. Run `forge init no_ignore`\r\n2. Add `ignore = ['**/*.sol']` to `[fmt]`\r\n3. Mess up formatting in `Counter.sol`\r\n4. If you run `forge fmt` from `no_ignore/`, `Counter.sol` will not be reformatted. If you run `forge fmt` from `no_ignore/src/`, it will be reformatted.",
